radiographic_examinations.findings: Opened sutures for a child with progressive postnatal craniosynostosis.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Fusion of all sutures at 5 years of age, along with thumbprinting and anterior fontanelle bulge.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Severe craniosynostosis with evidence of high intracranial pressure.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Indicated papilledema and dilated optic nerve sheaths.

radiographic_examinations.findings: Thumbprinting, anterior fontanelle prominence, and suture fusion.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Transition from normal to pathological findings over time.
